MatchedObjectDescriptor.QualificationSummary:
Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-11 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector. Specialized experience must demonstrate the following:
Experience applying intensive knowledge of administrative and financial management systems; Experience demonstrating advanced formulation of budget and estimates to support: plans, programs, and activities;
Experience reviewing and evaluating budget requests; control, and reporting of obligations and expenditures;
Experience performing or advising on work in any of the phases or systems of budget administration;
Experience performing development, determination, and interpretation of budgetary policies and practices. Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-09 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector. Specialized experience must demonstrate the following:
Experience applying knowledge of administrative and financial management systems;
Experience demonstrating formulation of budget and estimates to support: plans, programs, and activities;
Experience reviewing and evaluating budget requests; control, and reporting of obligations and expenditures;
Experience performing or advising on work in any of the phases or systems of budget administration;
Experience performing development, determination, and interpretation of budgetary policies and practices. Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management web site: https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series Experience refers to paid and unpaid experience, including volunteer work done through National Service programs (e.g., professional, philanthropic, religious, spiritual, community, student, social). Volunteer work helps build critical competencies, knowledge, and skills and can provide valuable training and experience that translates directly to paid employment.

Your resume must demonstrate at least one year of specialized experience at or equivalent to the GS-14 grade level or pay band in the Federal service or equivalent experience in the private or public sector performing most or all of the following duties.
Specialized experience must demonstrate the following:
1) Developing integrated, risk-informed and fiscally-balanced approaches with resource sponsors in planning defendable and executable Strategic Deterrence, readiness, capability and capacity programs into the Navy's annual POM submission;
2) Demonstrating expert knowledge of the Planning, Programming, Budgeting, and Execution (PPBE) process with both internal (OPNAV) and external (Fleet, CNIC, other Resource Sponsors, FMB, OSD, OMB, Congress) stakeholders;
3) Recommending and implementing new and revised financial management concepts, internal controls, methodologies, policies, and strategies in support of the organization's programs;
4) Planning and directing entire financial or budgeting systems for broad, emerging, or similarly critical large-scale department/agency wide programs of national or international scope;
5) Organizing employee workflow, monitoring employee productivity, and providing technical and administrative oversight, advice, and instruction. Additional qualification information can be found from the following Office of Personnel Management web site: https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/#url=List-by-Occupational-Series Experience refers to paid and unpaid experience, including volunteer work done through National Service programs (e.g., professional, philanthropic, religious, spiritual, community, student, social). Volunteer work helps build critical competencies, knowledge, and skills and can provide valuable training and experience that translates directly to paid employment.
